<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 4:31PM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An intense snow band will affect eastern Richland...
Medina...Wayne...southern Lorain...Holmes...Portage...southwestern
Trumbull...Mahoning...southern Huron...Ashland...Stark...Summit and
northeastern Knox Counties Until 600 PM EST....
At 429 PM EST, radar indicated an intense snow band along a line
extending from near Ravenna to 7 miles west of Savannah, moving
southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Winds to 30 mph...
Visibility rapidly dropping to less than a quarter of a mile...
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Canton, Youngstown, Mansfield, Medina, Wooster, Ashland,
Salem, Ravenna, Columbiana, Millersburg, Cuyahoga Falls, Boardman,
Brunswick, Massillon, Kent, Barberton, Green, Alliance, and Hudson.
Use extra caution if you must travel into or through this lake effect
snow band. Rapid changes in visibility and potentially slick roads
are likely to lead to accidents. Consider delaying travel until this
snow band passes your location.
To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/cle and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
&amp;&amp;
ODOT DMS  301, 305, 316, 327, 601, 602, 603, 606, 607, 608, 609, 610,
611, 612, 613, 614, 615, 616, 617, 618, 604, 605, and 619.</description>
